OLD PUNGGOL NASI LEMAK
Rice slight to moist type, fragrant is nice.
Ikan bilis, peanuts ok, portion quite little.
Fried chicken wing so so, maybe fried for awhile already.
Chillie more to sweet, it's nice.
$4.50 is reasonable üëç.

Very bad service. Visited today ( 29 March around 5pm plus) wanted to buy buns at the drink stall, the younger guy and older drink maker can pretend not to hear me and ignore. Come on, if they think that selling bun is beneath them, then go work in some top restaurants. By the way, the food there aren't fantastic too, going there because there was a heavy downpour.
The toast bread nice! But don‚Äôt have set, only ala cart price.
$2.20 for a milo kosong ice which tasted like coloured water (even before the ice melt)

One of the aunty at the drinks stall makes great toast! She put in effort to toast and make it nice but she's off on Thursday!  Got once the usual aunty was not around and toast was made by another lady & it tasted horribly bad and soggy. Unlike the usual aunty! If u like great kopi O and well toast bread, do come here & look for the aunty in hairbun (or tied up hair) usually cashier or making toast.
